    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Concussion idiophones consisting of two or more objects in the form of sticks, plaques, troughs, or vessels of wood, bone, ivory, shell or other hard sonorous material, sounded by striking together.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000000/VP</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000099620/Legacy AAT data</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Idiófonos de percusión que consisten en dos o más objetos en forma de varas, placas, artesas o vasijas de madera, hueso, marfil, concha u otro material sonoro duro, que suenan al golpearse entre sí.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>Spanish</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000131/CDBP-SNPC</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000051034/TAA database (2000-)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Slaginstrumenten bestaande uit twee of meer stokken, plaatjes, kommen of schaaltjes van hout, been, ivoor, schelp of een ander hard klinkend materiaal, die men laat klinken door ze tegen elkaar te slaan.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>Dutch</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000205/AAT-Ned</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000113770/AAT-Ned (1994-)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000052452/Encyclopedie van muziekinstrumenten (1977)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>由兩個以上棒狀、板狀、槽狀或器皿物體所組成的震擊發聲體鳴樂器，材質為木頭、骨頭、象牙、貝殼、或其他能發出聲音的堅硬材料，藉由相互敲擊發聲。</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>Chinese (traditional)</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000250/AS-Academia Sinica</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000079740/AS-Academia Sinica data (2014-)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Gegenschlagidiofon, bestehend aus zwei oder mehr Teilen in der Form von Stöcken, Tafeln oder Gefäßen aus Holz, Knochen, Elfenbein, Muschelschale oder einem anderen harten, tönenden Material; zum Klingen gebracht, indem die Teile gegeneinander geschlagen werden.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>German</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000232/IfM-SMB-PK</Contributor_id>
